The future of energy is digitised, decarbonised and localised. At Smartest Energy, we need revolutionary thinkers to help our customers make the most of this new landscape, thinking differently to find smart solutions to complex problems. Join us and help power the revolution.

Formed in 2001, we’re an agile business driven by entrepreneurial thinking. As a subsidiary of the Marubeni Corporation, we also have strong investment and infrastructure behind us. As well as our US office, we have three offices in the UK, and another in Australia. Further expansion will follow shortly which means big global career opportunities for you, with plenty of potential to explore new markets.
Overview
You will lead on the design, development and control of SmartestEnergy US’s data. You will develop knowledge of the underlying data and data products involved in the end to end business and operational processes and be responsible for engaging with business representatives and working closely with internal and external IT partners and vendors to assist in the translation of business requirements into application technical solutions and for their delivery across the portfolio of change initiatives and business processes.

In this position, you will be involved in the following:

Participate in analysis, validation and verification to determine what data is required to support business needs, where it is created, read, updated and deleted and the quality criteria associated with it;
Works with staff, vendors and customers to understand the business requirements to design the data architecture, solutions and processes;
Support wider team problem solving and analysis while balancing data, technology, business and operational issues to identify and deliver viable solutions;
Delivery of customised reports and recommendations to support on-going business decisions and customer reporting requirements;
Analysing large energy market data sets from multiple sources to enable business insights and data driven decision making;
Lead on the development of the critical data artefacts including data models (conceptual, logical and physical);
Ensure alignment of data artefacts through close working relationships with the business and operational stakeholders;
Develops specific metrics for quality and consistency reviews of data.

You are likely to have the following skills/experience:

Graduate in a relevant discipline or area;
Ability to rapidly comprehend the functions and capabilities of new technologies;
Can balance the long-term ("big picture") and short-term implications of individual decisions;
Ability to translate business and customer needs into data requirements;
The ability to communicate complex ideas in a clear, concise manner (verbal and written) across functional and technical departments
Work on multiple tasks at any one time, handling conflicting demands, prioritise workload and effectively delegate while maintaining high quality standards;
Sound judgement, attention to detail, accuracy, and follow-through on actions including the flexibility to perform in an ever-changing work environment;
High emotional resilience and good interpersonal and relationship building skills.

